"9 June 1583":"9 juni 1583","1608":"1608","Royston, Hertfordshire, England":"Royston, Hertfordshire, England","Bocking, Essex, England":"Bocking, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1554–20 October 1611":"about 1554–20 October 1611","1554–1611":"1554–1611","1554–1608":"1554–1608","1568–Female":"1568–Deceased","1580–Male":"1580–Deceased","1583–1621":"1583–1621","1535–Male":"1535–Deceased","1535–Female":"1535–Deceased","1583":"1583","1571":"1571","22 February 1568":"22 February 1568","1580":"1580","before 26 July 1608":"before 26 July 1608","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1568":"1568","1535":"1535","1600":"1600","1611":"1611","1621":"1621","1587":"1587","1554":"1554","20 October 1611":"20 October 1611","1585":"1585","about 1554":"about 1554","9 June 1583":"9 June 1583","1608":"1608","Royston, Hertfordshire, England":"Royston, Hertfordshire, England","Bocking, Essex, England":"Bocking, Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hewes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Essex):","variant of   Hughes  .","variant of   Hawes  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hughes","meanings":["English and Welsh: variant of   Hugh   with genitival or excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Irish and Scottish: adopted as an equivalent of Gaelic surnames based on the personal name <i>Aodh</i> ‘fire’, for example <b>Ó hAodha</b>, <b>Mac Aodha</b>; see   McCoy   and compare   McHugh  ."]}]},{"name":"Roger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name, <i>Rog(i)er</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705202,"age":4,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":15,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":17,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":31,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":33,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":46,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger Hewes was born about 1554, in Royston, Hertfordshire, England, his father, John Hewes, was 20 and his mother, Grace Waldron, was 20. He married Agnes in 1568, in Bocking, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died on 20 October 1611, in Bocking, Essex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 58, and was buried in Bocking, Essex, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1554–20 October 1611":"umbes 1554–20. oktoober 1611","1554–1611":"1554–1611","1554–1608":"1554–1608","1568–Female":"1568–Surnud","1580–Male":"1580–Surnud","1583–1621":"1583–1621","1535–Male":"1535–Surnud","1535–Female":"1535–Surnud","1583":"1583","1571":"1571","22 February 1568":"22. veebruar 1568","1580":"1580","before 26 July 1608":"enne 26. juulit 1608","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1568":"1568","1535":"1535","1600":"1600","1611":"1611","1621":"1621","1587":"1587","1554":"1554","20 October 1611":"20. oktoober 1611","1585":"1585","about 1554":"umbes 1554","9 June 1583":"9. juuni 1583","1608":"1608","Royston, Hertfordshire, England":"Royston, Hertfordshire, England","Bocking, Essex, England":"Bocking, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1554–20 October 1611":"noin 1554–20. lokakuuta 1611","1554–1611":"1554–1611","1554–1608":"1554–1608","1568–Female":"1568–Kuo